Package main.java.models

Class Car

java.lang.Object
main.java.models.Car
public class Car extends Object
Represents a car in a dealership system. This class stores information about a specific car model, including its specifications and availability.

  • Constructor Details

    • Car

      public Car(int capacity, String carType, int carsAvailable, String condition, String color, String id, int year, double price, String transmission, String vin, String fuelType, String model, boolean hasTurbo)
      Constructs a new Car instance with all necessary details including turbo information.
      Parameters:
      capacity - the seating capacity of the car
      carType - the type of the car (e.g., SUV, sedan)
      carsAvailable - the number of units available
      condition - the condition of the car (new or used)
      color - the color of the car
      id - a unique identifier for the car
      year - the manufacture year of the car
      price - the price of the car
      transmission - the type of transmission (automatic or manual)
      vin - the Vehicle Identification Number
      fuelType - the type of fuel the car uses (e.g., gasoline, diesel)
      model - the model name of the car
      hasTurbo - whether the car has a turbo feature

    • updateCarsAvailable

      public void updateCarsAvailable(boolean isIncrease, int amount)
      Updates the carsAvailable. Adds the "amount" value if isIncrease is True, and subtracts the "amount" value if isIncrease is false as it would then be a decrease.
      Parameters:
      isIncrease - boolean value, true if the number of carsAvailable is increasing.
      amount - the amount the carsAvailable is being increased or decreased by.
